d to our relationship with the narratives through which we view the human place in the natural world. By reframing environmental questions in terms of individual, social, and environmental narratives about flourishing, Emplotting Virtue offers a powerful vision of how we might remake our character so as to live more happily, more sustainably, and more virtuously in a diverse, beautiful, wondrous, and fragile world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aEnvironmental ethics. 0aEthics. 0aNarration (Rhetoric). 0aVirtue. 0aVirtues. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Environmental Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Ethics. 4aPhilosophy : Hermeneutics. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2014z978311149015140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143845119040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438451190423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438451190/original  a978-3-11-149015-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles